<p> I would sit around the simmering pot, impatiently waiting for the carrots to soften. I would then scoop them out with a ladle and eat them as a snack. I thought then, as I still do now, that eating those sweet, slightly softened carrots was one of life&#39;s great pleasures.</p>
<p>Thank you for celebrating the carrot in its purist form.</p>
