    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>The minute I saw this I knew I wanted to try it.  More a concept than a recipe.  It occurred to me that this would be terrific with any hardy vegetable.  So I used carrots, but also a lonely bit of cauliflower, and some remaining green beans.  And dried thyme instead of fresh (that&#39;s what I had).  The whole concept is brillian, but I especially loved the splash of vinegar.  I tried the dish before and after the splash, and it was a noticeable boost in flavor, and no one would know that I used vinegar.</p>
<p>I REALLY want to try this with beets.  Maybe mixed with the carrots.  The colors alone&#8230;.<br /><a href="http://improbablepantry.blogspot.com/" rel="nofollow">Improbable Pantry</a></p>
